Well, so, that's what I flew today.
First point of criticism: We need more attractive logbooks. Black is boring, pink is not really pink, but more like salmon-colored.
I wanted to fly ever since I was little.
And today it was so… I flew a plane today. I haven't fully processed that yet.
Data from FlightAware.
I'm trying to go again next Saturday. The weather doesn't look so good right now, but it's still Monday.
It's already becoming clear where the problems lie. It will probably be VERY difficult to obtain medical approval due to the FAA's stance on certain medications.
It's not impossible, but it will take VERY long and means A LOT of extra work.
That's certainly somewhat discouraging, but nevertheless just another problem that you have to solve. So far, it seems to be solvable. It just takes a lot of time and money.
If you want to know what awaits me.
The FAA is not a fan of ADHD. They definitely won't let you get a medical certificate if you're taking medication for it.
https://youtu.be/W5JSfq6LLAU?si=xIxPaY8ayqqNSj4c
If I were able to choose my own tail number for an airplane, you know it would definitely have to be a variant of N1337_, where _ stands for the last available letter.
It's logical that the sun shines when I'm gone, lol. Stupid cow.
